The paper discusses the use of supervised learning techniques for brain mapping using functional neuroimaging data. This falls under the intersection of computer science and neuroscience, with a focus on machine learning and image processing. The paper specifically mentions the use of sparse regression models, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of functional MRI data also suggests a potential fit with computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with small sample sizes and correlated variables, which are common issues in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.SI) research.
